                            <comment id="14348752" author="srowen" created="Thu, 5 Mar 2015 14:04:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think there are two ways to resolve this:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1) Replace all occurrences of &lt;tt&gt;spark-parent&lt;/tt&gt; with &lt;tt&gt;spark-parent_2.10&lt;/tt&gt;. Use the scripts to simply update this value too during release.&lt;br/&gt;
2) Remove use of &lt;tt&gt;spark.binary.version&lt;/tt&gt; where dependencies are expressed between modules, and hard-code &lt;tt&gt;2.10&lt;/tt&gt;, updated to &lt;tt&gt;2.11&lt;/tt&gt; during release. This would mean the parent POM no longer has to change between versions in order to get this right.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ll submit a PR both ways for consideration. I suppose I feel like #2 is actually nicer, if it works.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
